# Key Equations and Formulas

### Stationarity check: three conditions

$$E[Y_t] = \mu \quad \text{(constant mean)}$$

$$\text{Var}(Y_t) = \sigma^2 \quad \text{(constant variance)}$$

$$\text{Cov}(Y_t, Y_{t-k}) = \gamma_k \quad \text{(depends only on lag } k\text{, not on } t\text{)}$$

### First difference (to remove trend)

$$\Delta Y_t = Y_t - Y_{t-1}$$

### Log transformation (to stabilise variance)

$$\log(Y_t)$$

### Random walk equation

$$Y_t = Y_{t-1} + \varepsilon_t$$

### AR(p) model

$$Y_t = \phi_1 Y_{t-1} + \phi_2 Y_{t-2} + \cdots + \phi_p Y_{t-p} + \varepsilon_t$$

### MA(q) model

$$Y_t = \varepsilon_t + \theta_1 \varepsilon_{t-1} + \theta_2 \varepsilon_{t-2} + \cdots + \theta_q \varepsilon_{t-q}$$

### Significance bounds on ACF/PACF plots

$$\pm \frac{1.96}{\sqrt{n}}$$

